                <h1>Unraveling Conspiracy Theories: Truth or Fiction?</h1>
                <p>Conspiracy theories have long fascinated people, intertwining elements of mystery and skepticism. From government cover-ups to secret societies, they often challenge conventional narratives. While some find them thrilling, others promote paranoia. Understanding the psychology behind these beliefs is essential for discerning fact from fiction.</p>
